Description: Foot and floor sherd of East Greek pottery cup or bowl; low ring foot with broad resting surface; orange clay with silver mica; rosette of five leaves painted in tondo; brown band painted on outer face of foot; reserved underside; arrow sign cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 360)
Johnston 2006a / Trademarks on Greek Vases: Addenda (East Greek 191)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.211)
